
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates the use of the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a substring within a target string. It retrieves the target string, the substring to search for, and the replacement string using [get-value] expressions. The [strings.replace] slot then performs the replacement operation.
strings.replace:x:@.target-string
   get-value:x:@.search-for
   get-value:x:@.replace-with
